WEBVTT

00:00.834 --> 00:03.920
(high-pitched,
warbling static)

00:04.003 --> 00:05.422
(garbled radio transmission)

00:05.505 --> 00:07.257
(high-pitched,
electronic squealing)

00:11.386 --> 00:17.600
PUBLIC AFFAIRS OFFICER:
<i>Briefing number 1015060816.</i>

00:18.268 --> 00:21.271
<i>The</i> Bradbury Heavy <i> mission.</i>

00:21.354 --> 00:23.773
<i>Earth is a planet</i>
<i>of many wonders.</i>

00:23.857 --> 00:25.859
<i>A rare mix</i>
<i>of biological diversity</i>

00:25.942 --> 00:29.154
<i>and abundant resources.</i>

00:29.237 --> 00:31.156
<i>Humanity has always endeavored</i>

00:31.239 --> 00:34.534
<i>to explore and discover in the</i>
<i>face of even the longest odds.</i>

00:34.617 --> 00:38.163
<i>But the third planet</i>
<i>from Sol finds itself</i>

00:38.246 --> 00:40.957
<i>on the brink of catastrophe.</i>

00:41.040 --> 00:43.793
<i>Environmental changes</i>
<i>and political unrest</i>

00:43.877 --> 00:45.795
<i>has left Earth's</i>
<i>long-term prospects</i>

00:45.879 --> 00:47.797
<i>in a tenuous situation.</i>

00:47.881 --> 00:52.385
<i>As a result, new horizons have</i>
<i>grown increasingly appealing.</i>

00:55.221 --> 00:57.307
<i>All systems are go</i>
<i>for the first human flight</i>

00:57.390 --> 00:59.309
<i>to the planet Mars</i>

00:59.392 --> 01:02.312
<i>and the start of colonization</i>
<i>of the solar system.</i>

01:02.395 --> 01:04.147
<i>A large porthole is positioned</i>

01:04.230 --> 01:06.483
<i>over the center</i>
<i>flight commander seat.</i>

01:06.566 --> 01:08.818
<i>For launch</i>
<i>and until Mars landing,</i>

01:08.902 --> 01:11.988
<i>it is sealed and covered</i>
<i>to decrease radiation exposure.</i>

01:12.071 --> 01:13.990
(whirring)

01:14.073 --> 01:16.826
<i>The final air-to-ground</i>
<i>communication checks</i>

01:16.910 --> 01:19.370
<i>are conducted by Flight</i>
<i>Commander Alexa Brandt...</i>

01:19.454 --> 01:24.209
MLC.<i> Bradbury</i> confirms porthole
radiation shield closure nominal

01:24.292 --> 01:26.836
and secured for launch.

01:26.920 --> 01:29.380
PUBLIC AFFAIRS OFFICER:
<i>...and Pilot Casey Donlin.</i>

01:29.464 --> 01:31.132
TINA confirms

01:31.216 --> 01:34.886
all Near Earth Network
tracking frequencies are locked.

01:34.969 --> 01:38.515
{\an5}PUBLIC AFFAIRS OFFICER:
<i>Flight engineer Rei Tanaka</i>
<i>monitors onboard fuel cells</i>

01:38.598 --> 01:41.226
<i>preparing to transfer</i>
<i>to ship's internal power.</i>

01:41.309 --> 01:44.896
LCC.<i> Bradbury</i> reporting
six good APUs.

01:44.979 --> 01:46.356
{\an5}PUBLIC AFFAIRS OFFICER:
<i>Flight Surgeon</i>
<i>Katherine Langford</i>

01:46.439 --> 01:48.149
<i>monitors the crew vitals...</i>

01:48.233 --> 01:49.484
Jerry, this monitor's reading

01:49.567 --> 01:51.152
that you shouldn't have had
the cauliflower

01:51.236 --> 01:53.029
at the pre-launch dinner.

01:53.112 --> 01:54.531
{\an5}PUBLIC AFFAIRS OFFICER:
<i>...while Mission Specialist</i>
<i>Jerry Pierson</i>

01:54.614 --> 01:56.574
<i>awaits "all systems are go."</i>

01:56.658 --> 01:59.369
Well, when the ship launches,
I will, too, huh?

01:59.452 --> 02:02.038
{\an5}TINA: Performing OMS
tank repressurization.

02:02.121 --> 02:04.040
PUBLIC AFFAIRS OFFICER:
<i>They are aided by the onboard</i>

02:04.123 --> 02:07.085
<i>Transport Information Network</i>
<i>Artificial Intelligence unit,</i>

02:07.168 --> 02:09.378
<i>known as "TINA."</i>

02:09.461 --> 02:12.382
{\an5}LAUNCH CONTROL:
This is WTD conducting
launch status check.

02:12.465 --> 02:14.425
{\an5}As all stations verify
ready to resume count

02:14.509 --> 02:16.219
and "go" for launch,

02:16.302 --> 02:18.513
crew is advised to stand by.

02:18.596 --> 02:21.266
BRANDT:
Copy that. Crew standing by.

02:21.349 --> 02:25.895
TINA, mute communications
and play... "Family."

02:25.979 --> 02:29.399
(intro to "Family"
by The Interrupters plays)

02:29.482 --> 02:30.900
♪ I got a mother named Mary ♪

02:30.984 --> 02:32.235
CREW:
♪ I got a mother named Mary ♪

02:32.318 --> 02:34.279
♪ I got a brother named Barry ♪

02:34.362 --> 02:36.990
{\an5}CREW: ♪ I got a brother
named Barry... ♪

02:34.362 --> 02:36.990
LAUNCH CONTROL: BTC?

02:37.073 --> 02:38.241
{\an5}TEST CONTROLLER:
BTC... go.

02:37.073 --> 02:38.241
♪ And my uncle's name... ♪

02:38.324 --> 02:40.076
{\an5}LAUNCH CONTROL: LPS?

02:38.324 --> 02:40.076
LAUNCH PROCESSING: Go.

02:40.159 --> 02:42.078
{\an5}♪ He's in the military... ♪

02:40.159 --> 02:42.078
LAUNCH CONTROL: Safety console?

02:42.161 --> 02:44.998
{\an5}SAFETY CONSOLE: Safety is go.

02:42.161 --> 02:44.998
LAUNCH CONTROL: Range weather?

02:45.081 --> 02:46.916
{\an5}RANGE WEATHER:
Range weather has no constraints
for launch.

02:47.000 --> 02:48.918
{\an5}♪ And she's in the cemetery... ♪

02:47.000 --> 02:48.918
LAUNCH CONTROL: SRO?

02:49.002 --> 02:50.253
{\an5}SUPERINTENDENT RANGE OPERATION:
SRO is no-go.

02:50.336 --> 02:52.630
{\an5}Repeat, no-go!

02:50.336 --> 02:52.630
♪ My one... ♪

02:52.714 --> 02:56.301
(alarm blaring)

02:58.219 --> 02:59.596
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!

02:59.679 --> 03:00.930
{\an5}LAUNCH CONTROL:
SRO, repeat your status.

03:01.014 --> 03:02.932
♪ This is my family... ♪

03:03.016 --> 03:04.267
{\an5}TINA, music off.

03:03.016 --> 03:04.267
(music stops)

03:04.350 --> 03:06.102
SRO, explain your hold.

03:06.185 --> 03:08.146
{\an5}SUPERINTENDENT RANGE OPERATION:
At 02100...

03:08.229 --> 03:10.607
This is confirmed? Where?

03:10.690 --> 03:12.442
What is the confirmation?

03:12.525 --> 03:14.569
Beyond the EAS... Now!

03:14.652 --> 03:16.946
{\an5}Tell me the fucking
NASIC confirmation!

03:17.030 --> 03:19.449
Jesus Christ.

03:19.532 --> 03:22.285
LLC. SRO.

03:22.368 --> 03:24.621
{\an5}National Air and Space
Intelligence Center

03:24.704 --> 03:27.123
{\an5}has confirmed detection
of the launch of five long-range

03:27.206 --> 03:29.167
{\an5}Hwasong-14 ICBMs out of
the North Korean peninsula.

03:29.250 --> 03:31.002
Are you fucking kidding me?

03:31.085 --> 03:32.462
{\an5}Los Angeles and Seattle
have already been hit.

03:32.545 --> 03:34.130
Holy shit.

03:34.213 --> 03:35.465
{\an5}They have determined
Wells Spaceport is the target

03:35.548 --> 03:37.300
{\an5}of one missile's trajectory.

03:35.548 --> 03:37.300
Oh...

03:37.383 --> 03:39.552
{\an5}Delivery time,
launch to impact...

03:37.383 --> 03:39.552
What do we do?

03:39.636 --> 03:40.637
...30 minutes.

03:40.720 --> 03:41.971
What do we do?

03:42.055 --> 03:43.139
2100 was 20 minutes ago.

03:43.222 --> 03:45.683
Scheduled launch in nine.
That's a one-minute window.

03:45.767 --> 03:47.435
If we ditch now,
we can pop the hatch

03:47.518 --> 03:49.479
and be down on the ground
in about ten minutes.

03:49.562 --> 03:51.314
No, we'd be vaporized
by the 25th floor.

03:51.397 --> 03:53.524
If we abort now,
this ship suffers a direct hit.

03:53.608 --> 03:55.276
{\an5}If we launch...

03:53.608 --> 03:55.276
{\an1}DONLIN:
If we launch,

03:55.360 --> 03:56.611
we at least get the ship
out of harm's way.

03:56.694 --> 03:57.987
If we don't even try,
there's a possibility

03:58.071 --> 03:59.155
the human race ends
in ten minutes.

03:59.238 --> 04:01.366
{\an5}LAUNCH CONTROL:
<i>Bradbury.</i> LCC.

04:01.449 --> 04:03.618
{\an5}NASIC has advised us
to evacuate the facility.

04:03.701 --> 04:05.620
{\an5}SUPERINTENDENT RANGE OPERATION:
Peterson Air Force Base
is confirming

04:05.703 --> 04:08.665
{\an5}an American counterstrike--
45 Trident II missiles

04:08.748 --> 04:10.667
{\an5}against North Korean
and Russian targets.

04:10.750 --> 04:12.502
(electronic trilling)

04:12.585 --> 04:15.004
Abort or go?

04:15.088 --> 04:16.755
We have no choice.
We have to abort.

04:16.839 --> 04:19.300
I did not train

04:19.384 --> 04:20.677
for four years

04:20.760 --> 04:22.512
and give up my only family

04:22.595 --> 04:25.348
to be nuked on a launch pad.
Fucking go!

04:25.431 --> 04:27.058
{\an5}Katherine?

04:25.431 --> 04:27.058
Go.

04:27.141 --> 04:29.143
We should treat this
like every other cause

04:29.227 --> 04:30.728
for environmental evacuation
or hurricane

04:30.812 --> 04:31.688
{\an5}or an earthquake.

04:30.812 --> 04:31.688
Jerry?

04:31.771 --> 04:33.481
It...

04:33.564 --> 04:34.357
PIERSON:
Fuck.

04:34.440 --> 04:35.566
BRANDT:
Jerry?

04:35.650 --> 04:37.694
Go.

04:37.777 --> 04:39.320
You hesitated.

04:39.404 --> 04:42.198
Because how can this possibly
be happening?

04:42.281 --> 04:43.533
Four "go," one "no."

04:43.616 --> 04:45.535
So what is this,
fucking majority rules?

04:45.618 --> 04:47.161
No, it's not majority rules.

04:47.245 --> 04:49.664
I am commander of this mission.
<i>My</i> rules.

04:49.747 --> 04:51.124
{\an1}Continue
launch control protocols.

04:52.125 --> 04:54.335
LCC.<i> Bradbury.</i>

04:54.419 --> 04:55.712
{\an1}Transfer all
launch control function

04:55.795 --> 04:58.256
{\an3}and power to
internal <i> Bradbury.</i>

04:58.339 --> 05:00.216
(radio static)

05:00.299 --> 05:02.051
{\an5}LAUNCH CONTROL:
<i>Bradbury</i> transfer
to internal power

05:02.135 --> 05:04.053
{\an5}and launch control
in three, two,

05:04.137 --> 05:05.555
{\an5}one.

05:04.137 --> 05:05.555
Brandt?

05:05.638 --> 05:07.223
{\an5}Start.

05:05.638 --> 05:07.223
{\an1}DONLIN:
I'm sorry,

05:07.306 --> 05:09.267
{\an1}but we did not come
all this way

05:09.350 --> 05:11.394
to bail out.

05:11.477 --> 05:13.396
Go for auto sequence.

05:15.148 --> 05:17.233
Good luck, Launch Control.

05:17.316 --> 05:19.235
{\an5}LAUNCH CONTROL:
<i>Bradbury,</i> be advised.

05:19.318 --> 05:21.571
{\an5}From this point onward,
we are evacuating the facility

05:21.654 --> 05:23.573
{\an5}and will neither deliver
or receive commands

05:23.656 --> 05:25.241
from the launch vehicle.

05:25.324 --> 05:26.743
Godspeed,<i> Bradbury.</i>

05:26.826 --> 05:28.286
Lower visors.

05:28.369 --> 05:30.747
(whirring)

05:30.830 --> 05:34.250
{\an5}TINA: We are "go"
for auto sequence start.

05:34.334 --> 05:36.252
TINA,
go for main engine starter.

05:36.335 --> 05:38.838
Main engine ignition.

05:47.555 --> 05:50.224
{\an5}TINA:
Launch tower has been cleared.

05:55.730 --> 05:57.732
NARRATOR:
Five voyagers setting sail

05:57.815 --> 05:59.734
to a mysterious red light

05:59.817 --> 06:02.612
35 million miles
across an empty sea,

06:02.695 --> 06:05.448
soaring within the greatest
invention ever created

06:05.531 --> 06:09.285
by the human spirit to escape
a catastrophe made possible

06:09.368 --> 06:12.580
by the most destructive regions
of the human mind.

06:14.540 --> 06:16.459
Individual madness

06:16.542 --> 06:18.503
or shared nightmare?

06:18.586 --> 06:22.131
The answer lies
in their search for safe harbor

06:22.215 --> 06:26.260
here... in The Twilight Zone.

06:27.887 --> 06:29.472
<i>(The Twilight Zone</i> theme
playing)

06:29.555 --> 06:31.307
NARRATOR: <i> You're traveling</i>
<i>through another dimension,</i>

06:31.390 --> 06:34.644
<i>a dimension not only of</i>
<i>sight and sound but of mind.</i>

06:34.727 --> 06:37.814
<i>It is the middle ground</i>
<i>between light and shadow,</i>

06:37.897 --> 06:40.650
<i>between science</i>
<i>and superstition.</i>

06:40.733 --> 06:43.319
{\an8}<i>And it lies between</i>
<i>the pit of one's fears</i>

06:43.402 --> 06:46.155
{\an8}<i>and the summit</i>
<i>of one's knowledge.</i>

06:46.239 --> 06:49.325
<i>You are now traveling through</i>
<i>a dimension of imagination.</i>

06:49.408 --> 06:53.329
<i>You've just crossed over</i>
<i>into The Twilight Zone.</i>

06:58.709 --> 07:00.378
{\an5}TINA:
Trans-Mars injection
burn shutoff

07:00.461 --> 07:02.380
in E-minus ten minutes.

07:02.463 --> 07:05.258
{\an5}Approaching Earth escape
velocity.

07:07.760 --> 07:10.555
{\an9}Mission Command,
this is <i> Bradbury Heavy.</i>

07:10.638 --> 07:13.391
{\an8}Please respond.

07:13.474 --> 07:17.687
{\an8}Mission Command, this is
<i>Bradbury Heavy.</i> Respond.

07:17.770 --> 07:22.191
{\an8}Mission Command, this is
<i>Bradbury Heavy.</i> Respond.

07:22.275 --> 07:24.360
{\an8}(radio static)

07:24.443 --> 07:27.697
{\an8}MAN:
This is the Emergency
Alert System notification.

07:27.780 --> 07:29.365
{\an8}This is not a test.

07:29.448 --> 07:31.534
{\an8}A nuclear weapons attack
was commenced

07:31.617 --> 07:33.619
{\an8}against the United States.

07:43.379 --> 07:49.218
{\an8}TINA: TMI burn shutoff
in E-minus ten minutes.

07:49.302 --> 07:51.220
{\an8}MAN: Nuclear bombs
have been detonated

07:51.304 --> 07:53.514
{\an8}above several cities
across the country,

07:53.598 --> 07:56.225
{\an8}including Washington, D.C.,
New York City, Los Angeles...

07:56.309 --> 07:57.727
{\an8}Turn that off.

07:57.810 --> 08:01.397
{\an8}(radio turns off)

08:01.480 --> 08:04.984
{\an8}TINA: TMI burn shutoff
in E-minus nine minutes.

08:06.652 --> 08:08.571
{\an8}Yo, Pierson,

08:08.654 --> 08:10.573
{\an9}any chance we can eject
the porthole cover

08:10.656 --> 08:12.658
{\an8}to get a visual on below?

08:13.993 --> 08:16.412
{\an8}Is there anything left to see?

08:16.495 --> 08:18.289
{\an8}Answer the question.

08:18.372 --> 08:21.751
{\an8}(sighs) Yes, if we're gonna
remain in orbit.

08:21.834 --> 08:23.753
{\an8}No, if we're going on to Mars.

08:23.836 --> 08:25.588
{\an8}We're going to Mars in...

08:25.671 --> 08:28.049
{\an7}eight and a half minutes,
so, no.

08:30.968 --> 08:32.970
{\an8}I'd rather have a radiation
shield than a window.

08:33.054 --> 08:35.097
{\an9}The cameras
give us visuals.

08:39.684 --> 08:42.270
{\an8}Casey, we wanted this mission

08:42.355 --> 08:44.607
{\an8}since we were firsties
with RedElev squadron.

08:44.690 --> 08:48.903
{\an8}Pierson, you beat out,
what, 15,000 applicants?

08:48.986 --> 08:51.948
{\an8}15,380.

08:52.031 --> 08:54.283
{\an8}(chuckles)
Katie lost her marriage

08:54.367 --> 08:56.285
{\an8}accepting this mission.

08:56.369 --> 08:59.330
{\an8}And just a month ago, we were
all at Rei's father's funeral.

08:59.413 --> 09:02.458
{\an9}He was proud
she was going.

09:02.541 --> 09:04.460
{\an8}We all signed up knowing

09:04.543 --> 09:06.837
{\an8}it would be four years
till we came back.

09:06.921 --> 09:08.798
{\an8}And we knew during that time

09:08.881 --> 09:12.009
{\an8}that all of our loved ones would
wonder the rest of their lives

09:12.093 --> 09:13.594
{\an8}about us if something...

09:13.678 --> 09:15.680
{\an8}(voice breaking):
went wrong.

09:15.763 --> 09:18.516
{\an8}We just never envisioned we'd be
the ones wondering about them.

09:18.599 --> 09:22.937
{\an8}TINA: TMI burn shutoff
in E-minus six minutes.

09:23.020 --> 09:24.855
{\an8}Our options--

09:24.939 --> 09:26.857
{\an8}we orbit Earth
the rest of our lives,

09:26.941 --> 09:29.360
{\an8}burn up in the atmosphere
when our fuel runs out.

09:29.443 --> 09:30.987
{\an8}Food will run out
before the fuel.

09:31.070 --> 09:32.822
{\an8}We can try and reenter
through the command module.

09:32.905 --> 09:35.574
{\an8}You know the CM is designed
for a water landing.

09:35.658 --> 09:37.994
{\an7}No one'll be there
to fish us out.

09:38.077 --> 09:40.079
{\an8}We'll drown.

09:38.077 --> 09:40.079
{\an9}BRANDT:
So we go.

09:40.162 --> 09:43.332
{\an9}We travel the 218 days
and land on Mars.

09:43.416 --> 09:45.334
{\an9}TANAKA:
It's a suicide mission.

09:45.418 --> 09:47.878
{\an9}LANGFORD:
She's right.
We'd die there.

09:47.962 --> 09:50.673
{\an8}Yeah, we'd die of cancer and
prolonged radiation exposure

09:50.756 --> 09:53.342
{\an9}before we could have the
chance to refine enough fuel.

09:53.426 --> 09:58.097
{\an8}There's a test to the universe.

10:00.599 --> 10:02.852
A scientific theory,
made by an economist,

10:02.935 --> 10:05.021
known as "The Great Filter."

10:06.772 --> 10:08.357
The Great Filter posits

10:08.441 --> 10:12.695
that life in the universe
is very, very rare.

10:12.778 --> 10:15.698
It's hard to start,
harder to continue.

10:15.781 --> 10:17.950
The test of life

10:18.034 --> 10:21.370
is, "Can an advanced
life-form make it

10:21.454 --> 10:23.831
to another planet
before it destroys itself?"

10:25.958 --> 10:28.753
Most advanced life fails.

10:30.463 --> 10:32.965
{\an3}That's why we never encounter
any other civilizations.

10:34.967 --> 10:38.679
They destroy themselves
before we can reach 'em.

10:41.766 --> 10:45.394
Humans... Earth...

10:45.478 --> 10:47.605
we're on the brink.

10:48.981 --> 10:50.733
This mission was designed

10:50.816 --> 10:54.612
because we had no choice
but to find a way out.

10:54.695 --> 10:59.909
{\an5}TINA: TMI burn shutoff
in E-minus five minutes.

10:59.992 --> 11:02.953
We go, and we go together.

11:03.037 --> 11:05.164
If we remain who we are,

11:05.247 --> 11:07.708
hold on
to the group's original goal,

11:07.792 --> 11:10.127
to the world's goal for us,

11:10.211 --> 11:12.588
{\an3}if we stick to what we
believed would get us there

11:12.671 --> 11:14.757
over the last four years--

11:14.840 --> 11:18.427
the stuff that makes us
a family-- I know we'll be okay.

11:18.511 --> 11:19.929
(sniffles)

11:20.012 --> 11:21.889
And if anyone is alive at home,

11:21.972 --> 11:24.642
maybe word will get out
that we made it.

11:24.725 --> 11:29.563
They can look up and see Mars,
and have hope for themselves.

11:29.647 --> 11:32.608
{\an5}TINA:
Go for Stage 3 TMI burn shutoff

11:32.692 --> 11:37.113
{\an5}in E-minus four minutes,
35 seconds.

11:40.741 --> 11:43.744
Tanaka, you copy TINA?

11:43.828 --> 11:46.831
Rei, do you copy?

11:48.874 --> 11:51.127
If you won't do it, I will.

11:51.210 --> 11:53.129
{\an1}BRANDT:
Rei,

11:53.212 --> 11:55.131
shut off TMI now.

11:57.258 --> 11:58.968
{\an3}TANAKA:
Orbital altitude

11:59.051 --> 12:01.637
1,124 kilometers.

12:01.721 --> 12:04.473
{\an5}TINA:
Go for second stage ejection
in E-minus ten seconds.

12:04.557 --> 12:05.933
{\an3}Speed--

12:06.016 --> 12:07.977
27,744 KPH.

12:08.060 --> 12:10.479
{\an5}TINA:
Two, one.

12:10.563 --> 12:12.481
Second stage ejection.

12:12.565 --> 12:15.025
(clacking)

12:15.109 --> 12:17.945
Earth escape velocity achieved.

12:18.028 --> 12:21.782
{\an5}Go for Trans-Mars injection
in four minutes, 30 seconds.

12:21.866 --> 12:23.701
TINA, deploy tethered SAT one.

12:23.784 --> 12:26.579
{\an5}TINA:
Deploying tethered SAT one.

12:30.207 --> 12:31.876
Tethered SAT one
