for it. You know that.

24:07.404 --> 24:09.364
{\an3}Commander.

24:11.950 --> 24:14.452
Commander, look...

24:16.413 --> 24:18.331
I'm sorry.

24:18.415 --> 24:20.000
And it is not like me...

24:20.083 --> 24:22.043
We cannot afford any accidents.

24:22.127 --> 24:25.172
{\an3}We cannot take on
any additional crew.

24:25.255 --> 24:27.382
We cannot risk any children.

24:27.465 --> 24:29.467
Ma'am, we've been very careful.

24:29.551 --> 24:31.553
The commander's right.

24:32.971 --> 24:36.057
The ship's supply
is painstakingly estimated.

24:36.141 --> 24:39.686
It's 3,200 calories a day
for a five-person crew, so...

24:41.271 --> 24:43.523
{\an3}If Tanaka had to
begin breastfeeding,

24:43.607 --> 24:45.901
{\an3}her caloric intake
would need to increase.

24:45.984 --> 24:47.861
Now you care about my life?

24:47.944 --> 24:51.072
You didn't care about my life
at launch or at TMI

24:51.156 --> 24:53.366
{\an3}or now.

25:19.184 --> 25:21.144
You all right?

25:22.187 --> 25:24.522
{\an1}We're officially
halfway there.

25:26.524 --> 25:29.903
I know Michael wanted a divorce

25:29.986 --> 25:31.905
{\an1}when you accepted
this mission.

25:31.988 --> 25:33.615
I asked you if you were okay.

25:33.698 --> 25:35.742
Do you regret it?

25:40.705 --> 25:43.625
I had a choice...

25:43.708 --> 25:47.712
{\an3}between Mike and a
round-trip ticket to Mars.

25:50.590 --> 25:52.592
I got neither.

26:03.228 --> 26:05.647
Tell me about your nightmare.

26:06.690 --> 26:08.692
(chuckles)

26:10.360 --> 26:12.612
I'm asleep.

26:12.696 --> 26:14.698
Then dreaming.

26:15.740 --> 26:17.742
Home.

26:18.576 --> 26:22.080
At my parents' place
in San Diego.

26:24.082 --> 26:26.459
Sky is blue.

26:26.543 --> 26:28.461
{\an1}Ocean.

26:28.545 --> 26:30.463
Natalie's there.

26:30.547 --> 26:34.301
<i>All my family's there.</i>

26:34.384 --> 26:36.303
And then I realize,

26:36.386 --> 26:38.638
in the dream,

26:38.722 --> 26:40.640
that I'm just dreaming,

26:40.724 --> 26:43.310
{\an1}that I'm
not really there.

26:43.393 --> 26:45.979
I don't want
to wake up.

26:46.062 --> 26:48.398
But I do.

26:50.734 --> 26:53.028
This...

26:53.111 --> 26:55.363
is the nightmare.

26:55.447 --> 26:58.366
You're not alone.

26:58.450 --> 27:00.368
We're in this.

27:00.452 --> 27:02.537
{\an3}With you.

27:02.620 --> 27:05.415
You're our commander.

27:07.292 --> 27:10.253
We're a family,
and we need our mum.

27:13.423 --> 27:16.718
You're the mom.

27:16.801 --> 27:21.598
I'm commander of nothing
but a slow suicide.

27:31.816 --> 27:34.027
{\an5}TANAKA:
This is Whipple Mars Mission
<i>Bradbury.</i>

27:34.110 --> 27:35.612
If anybody can hear me
on this frequency,

27:35.695 --> 27:38.239
go to Distress Relay Alert.
Come in.

27:38.323 --> 27:40.241
Radio signal's
taking longer.

27:40.325 --> 27:42.744
{\an3}Four minutes to Earth,
the closer we get to Mars.

27:42.827 --> 27:44.579
This is Whipple
Mars Mission <i> Bradbury.</i>

27:44.662 --> 27:46.247
Anybody receiving
this transmission,

27:46.331 --> 27:47.707
{\an3}go to Distress
Relay Alert.

27:47.791 --> 27:49.542
{\an3}Rei.

27:49.626 --> 27:51.753
{\an3}Commander
gave the order.

27:51.836 --> 27:55.799
