TINA: Alert. Alert.

35:17.031 --> 35:20.535
{\an5}Coronal mass ejection
detected on the sun deck.

35:20.618 --> 35:24.205
{\an5}Solar flare
estimated classification

35:24.288 --> 35:26.541
X8.5.

35:26.624 --> 35:28.876
An X8.5 solar flare
would wipe out TINA.

35:28.960 --> 35:29.961
And that would wipe out us.

35:30.044 --> 35:31.546
Suspend pseudo-gravity

35:31.629 --> 35:32.713
and position the heat shield

35:32.797 --> 35:33.881
{\an1}90 degrees
toward the Sun

35:33.965 --> 35:35.049
for the duration of the flare.

35:35.132 --> 35:36.217
Uh, I got news for you.

35:36.300 --> 35:37.510
{\an3}None of this
is real.

35:37.593 --> 35:39.178
It's just a test.

35:39.262 --> 35:42.181
None of this is real.
(chuckles)

35:42.265 --> 35:43.182
{\an3}None of it.

35:43.266 --> 35:44.809
{\an3}All right.

35:45.810 --> 35:48.020
It's just a test.

35:48.104 --> 35:49.021
(gasping)

35:58.823 --> 36:00.575
(alarm blaring)

36:00.658 --> 36:02.785
My hypothesis is such
that the events on this ship

36:02.869 --> 36:06.747
are the result of an endurance
simulation experiment

36:06.831 --> 36:08.791
meant to test crew morale

36:08.875 --> 36:10.710
and mental durability
during a trip to Mars.

36:10.793 --> 36:14.046
Unlike other such experiments,
we were not informed

36:14.130 --> 36:16.173
in order to get
a truer result.

36:16.257 --> 36:19.844
Okay, to test my hypothesis,
first, I made a calculation.

36:19.927 --> 36:22.096
{\an1}The probability
of a North Korean missile launch

36:22.179 --> 36:23.598
{\an1}just 20 minutes prior
to the launch

36:23.681 --> 36:24.932
{\an5}of the <i> Bradbury...</i>

36:23.681 --> 36:24.932
Jerry...

36:25.016 --> 36:28.936
The result was 735.6

36:29.020 --> 36:32.064
{\an5}<i>billion,</i> with a "B."

36:29.020 --> 36:32.064
TINA: Exposure levels fatal.

36:32.148 --> 36:33.608
{\an5}BRANDT: Pierson! Langford!

36:32.148 --> 36:33.608
{\an1}PIERSON: So, essentially,
an impossibility.

36:33.691 --> 36:35.276
Tanaka! Secure yourselves

36:35.359 --> 36:37.153
{\an5}in the flight deck!

36:35.359 --> 36:37.153
So the most likely
explanation is

36:37.236 --> 36:40.239
that we never launched.
(chuckles)

36:40.323 --> 36:41.741
{\an3}While we were
boarding the ship,

36:41.824 --> 36:43.743
we were redirected
in the launch tower tunnel

36:43.826 --> 36:44.911
to a <i> replica</i>

36:44.994 --> 36:45.912
<i>Bradbury</i> housed

36:45.995 --> 36:47.997
{\an3}in a facility on the
Whipple Spaceport campus.

36:48.080 --> 36:48.873
Jerry, we have to get
to the cockpit.

36:48.956 --> 36:50.917
Growing suspicious
just after launch,

36:51.000 --> 36:52.752
I was prescient enough
to conduct an experiment

36:52.835 --> 36:55.087
{\an5}just prior to TMI.

36:52.835 --> 36:55.087
Pierson, sit the fuck down, man!

36:55.171 --> 36:56.756
Jerry, I understand, and
you are making complete sense.

36:56.839 --> 36:58.633
{\an1}But can you tell me
from your flight seat?

36:58.716 --> 37:00.801
{\an5}TINA:
O2 fans disabled.

37:00.885 --> 37:04.639
I held a tablet stylus
in the air and released it.

37:04.722 --> 37:05.306
See? Rei.

37:05.389 --> 37:06.682
{\an3}(chuckles)
If it floated,

37:06.766 --> 37:07.934
then we <i> were</i> in orbit

37:08.017 --> 37:09.644
{\an5}and not in a simulation.

37:08.017 --> 37:09.644
{\an1}Jerry,

37:09.727 --> 37:10.853
you are endangering everyone.

37:10.937 --> 37:12.396
You have to get
to your flight seat.

37:13.397 --> 37:14.065
{\an1}Standing by
for a 90-degree

37:14.148 --> 37:15.650
{\an5}roll maneuver!

37:14.148 --> 37:15.650
BRANDT: Shit.

37:15.733 --> 37:17.652
Pierson,
get in your fucking chair now!

37:17.735 --> 37:19.987
Against my expectations,

37:20.071 --> 37:22.323
the stylus demonstrated the
properties of weightlessness.

37:22.406 --> 37:25.660
{\an5}TINA: Solar flare impact
in E-minus 273 seconds.

37:22.406 --> 37:25.660
So,

37:25.743 --> 37:26.827
{\an3}obviously,

37:26.911 --> 37:28.287
we are housed in

37:28.371 --> 37:30.957
a six degrees
of freedom simulator.

37:31.040 --> 37:34.627
We're capable of performing
the six types of motion possible

37:34.710 --> 37:36.170
by a rigid body
in three-dimensional space.

37:36.253 --> 37:38.130
Surge. Heave. Sway.
Yaw. Pitch. Roll.

37:38.214 --> 37:40.341
{\an5}Initiating heat shield.

37:38.214 --> 37:40.341
{\an3}All of this
against our wills

37:40.424 --> 37:43.177
or even our knowledge.
Now, I remain uncertain

37:43.260 --> 37:45.721
{\an1}at which point they redirected
us into the replica.

37:45.805 --> 37:47.306
{\an1}In the tunnel to the launch pad
is most likely.

37:47.390 --> 37:49.308
{\an1}But with a simulation
this sophisticated,

37:49.392 --> 37:51.268
who knows how long
we've been unaware?

37:51.352 --> 37:52.853
Jerry, I understand.
And I believe you, okay?

37:52.937 --> 37:53.854
I believe you...

37:53.938 --> 37:54.814
No, fuck you!

37:54.897 --> 37:56.691
{\an3}(laughs)

37:56.774 --> 37:58.025
You don't believe me!

37:58.109 --> 37:59.986
{\an3}You want me to do
what they want.

38:00.069 --> 38:05.157
{\an1}They made us think
that our families are dead!

38:05.241 --> 38:07.868
They made us think
that the Earth was destroyed.

38:07.952 --> 38:11.414
They fucked with eight months
of our lives,

38:11.497 --> 38:13.416
and I saw them watching us!

38:13.499 --> 38:15.376
{\an5}TINA:
Heat shield off-line.

38:15.459 --> 38:18.004
I saw them on the monitor!

38:18.087 --> 38:21.132
They are watching us
do their test!

38:22.425 --> 38:23.926
Shit.

38:24.010 --> 38:25.219
They are watching us!

38:25.302 --> 38:26.887
{\an3}They're
watching us.

38:26.971 --> 38:30.850
Impact in E-minus 188 seconds.

38:30.933 --> 38:33.519
They are watching us.

38:33.602 --> 38:34.520
No, you don't.
(chuckles)

38:34.603 --> 38:35.563
ET liquid leaking.

38:35.646 --> 38:38.190
No, you don't.
No, you don't.

38:38.274 --> 38:39.942
Pierson's fucking lost it.

38:40.026 --> 38:41.986
I'm right! I'm right!

38:42.069 --> 38:44.530
Unable to stop ET liquid leak.

38:44.613 --> 38:46.449
{\an5}Sit down!

38:44.613 --> 38:46.449
This toilet has

38:46.532 --> 38:49.035
a disposal device comprised
of plastic collection bags,

38:49.118 --> 38:50.870
which, although tied up
and stored for ejection

38:50.953 --> 38:52.204
into the vacuum of space,

38:52.288 --> 38:53.914
{\an5}consistently released

38:52.288 --> 38:53.914
Jerry, please!

38:53.998 --> 38:55.041
a thin two-micron fecal water...

38:55.124 --> 38:57.877
We need to position
the heat shield toward the Sun!

38:57.960 --> 38:58.836
{\an1}...vapor from
the trash bags,

38:58.919 --> 39:00.921
which, over a 12-week period
of approximately

39:01.005 --> 39:02.548
{\an1}five to ten fecal collections
a day, thus five to ten

39:02.631 --> 39:03.382
interactions with a vacuum,

39:03.466 --> 39:05.468
should create
a crystallizing ring

39:05.551 --> 39:08.554
of approximately ten microns
around the internal...

39:08.637 --> 39:12.391
Katherine, leave him!

39:12.475 --> 39:13.809
Lf is the latent heat
of freezing,

39:13.893 --> 39:16.270
{\an4}Ls is the latent heat
of sublimation...

39:13.893 --> 39:16.270
TINA: MILA alignment incomplete.

39:16.353 --> 39:18.064
{\an3}...and R is the radius
of the droplets

39:18.147 --> 39:19.398
{\an6}or the plastic
collection bags.

39:18.147 --> 39:19.398
TINA, calculate portside

39:19.482 --> 39:20.566
{\an5}orbital maneuver!

39:19.482 --> 39:20.566
{\an3}But there

39:20.649 --> 39:22.651
is nothing!

39:25.029 --> 39:26.614
There's nothing.

39:26.697 --> 39:27.948
Heat shield repositioned.

39:28.032 --> 39:29.241
There is nothing!

39:29.325 --> 39:32.411
I took samples for 105 days

39:32.495 --> 39:35.289
with my bare fucking hands,

39:35.373 --> 39:38.167
and there has never been a ring!

39:38.250 --> 39:39.126
All right, there has

39:39.210 --> 39:40.294
never been condensation!

39:40.377 --> 39:41.962
There has never been
crystallization!

39:42.046 --> 39:43.964
Where Z equals zero,

39:44.048 --> 39:45.174
there is nothing.

39:45.257 --> 39:47.093
{\an5}TINA:
All systems are go.

39:47.176 --> 39:48.969
We're in a six degrees
of freedom simulator...

39:49.053 --> 39:49.929
(electronic crackling)

39:50.012 --> 39:51.597
{\an3}...where they control
the video we see,

39:51.680 --> 39:53.933
they control the audio we hear,

39:54.016 --> 39:56.268
(crying):
and they are watching us.

39:56.352 --> 39:58.437
They're watching us.

39:58.521 --> 40:02.525
{\an5}TINA: OMB burn duration
will be three seconds.

40:02.608 --> 40:04.735
Okay, I will prove it.
(laughs)

40:14.453 --> 40:16.997
{\an5}Solar flare impact
in 15 seconds...

40:14.453 --> 40:16.997
He's opened the air lock.

40:17.081 --> 40:19.458
He's gonna get sucked out
into the vacuum of space.

40:19.542 --> 40:21.127
Not just into the
vacuum of space,

40:21.210 --> 40:23.129
{\an3}but into a fucking
solar flare.

40:23.212 --> 40:26.298
{\an5}TINA: Solar flare impact
in ten seconds.

40:26.382 --> 40:30.511
Stand by for OMB burn in ten...

40:30.594 --> 40:32.680
nine, eight,

40:32.763 --> 40:34.682
seven, six,

40:34.765 --> 40:37.643
five, four,

