Jerry lost that.

45:15.546 --> 45:17.673
{\an1}His body will
float around in space

45:17.756 --> 45:20.092
{\an1}long after the last star
has gone dark.

45:20.175 --> 45:23.887
He's the loneliest man
there will ever be.

45:23.971 --> 45:26.807
{\an1}So don't
romanticize Jerry.

45:26.890 --> 45:28.934
Don't make him a legend.

45:30.727 --> 45:34.606
Don't any of you walk out
that door expecting to be home.

45:34.690 --> 45:38.068
{\an1}'Cause we're not that,
we're not him.

45:38.152 --> 45:40.737
{\an1}And we may not
have a home.

45:42.739 --> 45:45.159
But we have each other.

45:46.577 --> 45:48.745
We're family.

